inline-math LaTex equation

Bayes formula written two ways in latex

\[ P({A } | { B}) = \frac{P({B} | { A}) \times P({A})}{P({B})} \]

\[ P(\textrm{A } | \textrm{ B}) = \frac{P(\textrm{B } | \textrm{ A}) \times P(\textrm{A})}{P(\textrm{B})} \]

Basic mermaid diagram with code found here2

flowchart LR
  A[Hard edge] --> B(Round edge)
  B --> C{Decision}
  C --> D[Result one]
  C --> E[Result two]

here is a mermaid diagram that I altered myself - I only went a couple layers deep

flowchart LR
 A(Plate Appearance in Baseball)
 A --> B{Pitch is thrown}
 B --> C{Strike}
 B --> D{Ball}
 B --> E(Ball in Play)
 C --> C1{Strike}
 C --> D1{Ball}
 C --> E1(Ball in Play)
 D --> C2{Strike}
 D --> D2{Ball}
 D --> E2(Ball in Play)
 C1 --> C3(Strikeout)
 C1 --> D3{Ball}
 C1 --> E3(Ball in Play)
 C1 --> F{Foul Ball}
